    <item>
      <title>PL/SQL - How to Remove Trailing Zeros but Keep Leading Zero</title>
      <link>http://edwardmanning.com/2014/02/21/plsql-how-to-remove-trailing-zeros-but-keep-leading-zero/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Feb 2014 11:49:59 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://edwardmanning.com/2014/02/21/plsql-how-to-remove-trailing-zeros-but-keep-leading-zero/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;WITH T AS
    (
      SELECT 100 AS EXAMPLE FROM DUAL
      UNION
      SELECT 98.336 AS EXAMPLE FROM DUAL
      UNION
      SELECT 25 AS EXAMPLE FROM DUAL
    )&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;SELECT 
  EXAMPLE / 100 AS EXAMPLE_1,
  TO_CHAR(EXAMPLE / 100) AS EXAMPLE_2,
  RTRIM(TO_CHAR(EXAMPLE / 100, &#39;FM0.999999999999&#39;), &#39;.&#39;) AS EXAMPLE_3
FROM T;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://edwardmanning.com/static/2014/02/plsql-leading-trailing-zeros.png&#34; alt=&#34;PL/SQL leading zero with no trailing zeros&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks to &lt;a href=&#34;https://community.oracle.com/message/9625400&#34;&gt;Oracle Community&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
